It's been a while since i've fiddled with those atomizer heads; When you unscrew the head from the tank, on the head you should be able to pop off the top part, exposing the coil and wick.
If you see that it's really black or super gunked up you might consider replacing the coil or [\(clean and dry burning it\)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aY3NqqEg_pw hd=1)
If it looks ok, you can add a drop of juice or two directly onto the coil and snap the top and bottom part back together.
Raising the voltage shouldn't damage the coil, what might happen is that juice will vaporize faster than the wick can bring new juice to the coil causing that burning taste. So you may need to take shorter hits at higher voltages.
